This paper deals with natural language models and machine learning tasks, which are typically associated with the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), databases (cs.DB), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of hash functions and Bloom filters is also relevant to the sub-category of cryptography (cs.CR), but this is less likely given the focus on machine learning tasks.
